1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,725
Advanced function concepts in JavaScript include higher-order functions and closures

2
00:00:05,250 --> 00:00:07,975
adding powerful functional programming capabilities

3
00:00:09,025 --> 00:00:13,775
Higher-order functions accept other functions as arguments or return them as results

4
00:00:14,175 --> 00:00:16,875
allowing for more abstract and flexible code

5
00:00:17,863 --> 00:00:18,312
Closures

6
00:00:18,425 --> 00:00:19,387
on the other hand

7
00:00:19,587 --> 00:00:21,762
are functions that remember their environment

8
00:00:22,075 --> 00:00:23,375
even after they are called

9
00:00:23,587 --> 00:00:25,837
enabling excellent use of private data

10
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:30,038
Both concepts form the backbone of many JavaScript patterns

11
00:00:30,325 --> 00:00:32,337
such as function chaining and currying

12
00:00:32,675 --> 00:00:35,562
which increase code efficiency and maintainability

